## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="3486e-102"><xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SemanticValue> é o objeto principal que implementa a tecnologia de semântica de System. Speech.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="3486e-102"><xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SemanticValue> is the primary object that implements the semantic technology in System.Speech.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="3486e-103">Interpretação de semântica permite gramáticas definir regras para uso por um mecanismo de reconhecimento para interpretar corretamente a entrada de áudio.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="3486e-103">Semantic interpretation allows grammars to define rules for use by a recognition engine to correctly interpret audio input.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="3486e-104">Interpretação de semântica também permite que os mecanismos de reconhecimento organizar seus resultados para que eles possam ser processados com mais facilidade, em vez de retornar reconhecidas apenas palavras e as sequências de palavras.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="3486e-104">Semantic interpretation also enables recognition engines to organize their results so that they can be more easily processed, rather than returning only recognized words and sequences of words.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="3486e-105">Por exemplo, o mecanismo de reconhecimento de saída "Alterar o plano de fundo para vermelho" precisaria ser analisados e interpretados por um aplicativo antes que ele possa ser usado.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="3486e-105">For example, the recognition engine output "Change background to red" would have to be parsed and interpreted by an application before it could be acted upon.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="3486e-106">Um <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.Grammar> objeto pode especificar uma interpretação de semântica para acelerar o processamento mais clara, especificando que a frase tem dois subestruturas semânticas, uma para selecionar o plano de fundo ou primeiro plano (representado pelo texto "em segundo plano") e outra para selecionar cor (representado pelo texto "red").</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="3486e-106">A <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.Grammar> object can specify a semantic interpretation to make processing clearer by specifying that the phrase has two semantic substructures, one for selecting background or foreground (represented by the text "background"), and the other for selecting color (represented by the text "red").</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="3486e-107">System. Speech representa a semântica de uma operação de reconhecimento em uma árvore de <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SemanticValue> objetos.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="3486e-107">System.Speech represents the semantics of a recognition operation in a tree of <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SemanticValue> objects.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="3486e-108">Cada <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SemanticValue> instância inclui o seguinte:</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="3486e-108">Each <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SemanticValue> instance includes the following:</span></span>  
  
-   <span data-ttu-id="3486e-109">Uma <xref:System.Object>, acessado por meio das <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SemanticValue.Value%2A> propriedade, usada para a chave da instância da <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SemanticValue>.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="3486e-109">An <xref:System.Object>, accessed by means of the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SemanticValue.Value%2A> property, used to key the instance of the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SemanticValue>.</span></span>  
  
-   <span data-ttu-id="3486e-110">Uma medida da precisão da análise semântica, retornado pelo <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SemanticValue.Confidence%2A> propriedade.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="3486e-110">A measure of the accuracy of semantic parsing, returned by the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SemanticValue.Confidence%2A> property.</span></span>  
  
-   <span data-ttu-id="3486e-111">Uma coleção de pares nome/valor (<xref:System.Collections.Generic.KeyValuePair%602>) de objetos filho, que também são <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SemanticValue> instâncias.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="3486e-111">A collection of name/value pairs (<xref:System.Collections.Generic.KeyValuePair%602>) of child objects, which are also <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SemanticValue> instances.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="3486e-112">Nós filho são acessíveis por meio de <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SemanticValue> implementação de <xref:System.Collections.Generic.IDictionary%602> usando uma chave de pesquisa de cadeia de caracteres e um <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SemanticValue> instância, como no exemplo a seguir.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="3486e-112">Child nodes are accessible through the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SemanticValue> implementation of <xref:System.Collections.Generic.IDictionary%602> using a string lookup key and a <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SemanticValue> instance, as in the following example.</span></span>  
  
    ```csharp  
    foreach (KeyValuePair<String, SemanticValue> child in semantics)   
    {  
      Utils.CreateSemanticsTreeNodes(semanticsNode.Nodes, child.Value, child.Key);  
    }  
    ```  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="3486e-113">Mecanismos de reconhecimento de com base em System. Speech fornecem instâncias válidas de <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SemanticValue> para todas as saídas de reconhecimento, até mesmo para frases com nenhuma estrutura semântica explícita.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="3486e-113">Recognition engines based on System.Speech provide valid instances of <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SemanticValue> for all output from recognition, even for phrases with no explicit semantic structure.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="3486e-114">O <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SemanticValue> da instância para uma frase é obtida usando o <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognizedPhrase.Semantics%2A> propriedade no <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognizedPhrase> objeto (ou objetos que herdam dele, como <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognitionResult>).</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="3486e-114">The <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SemanticValue> instance for a phrase is obtained using the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognizedPhrase.Semantics%2A> property on the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognizedPhrase> object (or objects that inherit from it, such as <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.RecognitionResult>).</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="3486e-115"><xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SemanticValue> objetos obtidos para frases reconhecidos sem estrutura semântica são caracterizados por:</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="3486e-115"><xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SemanticValue> objects obtained for recognized phrases without semantic structure are characterized by:</span></span>  
  
-   <span data-ttu-id="3486e-116">A falta de filhos (<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SemanticValue.Count%2A> é 0).</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="3486e-116">The lack of children (<xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SemanticValue.Count%2A> is 0).</span></span>  
  
-   <span data-ttu-id="3486e-117">A propriedade <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SemanticValue.Value%2A> é `null`.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="3486e-117">The <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SemanticValue.Value%2A> property is `null`.</span></span>  
  
-   <span data-ttu-id="3486e-118">Um nível de confiança de semântica artificiais de 1,0 (retornado por <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SemanticValue.Confidence%2A>).</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="3486e-118">An artificial semantic confidence level of 1.0 (returned by <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SemanticValue.Confidence%2A>).</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="3486e-119">Normalmente, os aplicativos criam <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SemanticValue> instâncias indiretamente, adicioná-los à <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.Grammar> objetos usando <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SemanticResultValue> e <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SemanticResultKey> instâncias, em conjunto com <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.Choices> e <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.GrammarBuilder> objetos.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="3486e-119">Typically, applications create <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SemanticValue> instances indirectly, adding them to <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.Grammar> objects by using <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SemanticResultValue> and <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SemanticResultKey> instances,  in conjunction with  <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.Choices> and <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.GrammarBuilder> objects.</span></span>  
  
